<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-03T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="324" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d324">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Belgium/173: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-03T17:00:00-05:00">December
                                    3, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>80. Your despatch No. 641, November 18. Your efforts and those of Mr.
                            Sussdorff to obtain cooperation in suppression of smuggling are greatly
                            appreciated.</p>
                        <p>Question of approaching other exporting nations receiving
                            consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>